definition[0]: a nameless person is someone whose name is not known
example[0]: the work of some nameless 13th-century writer
definition[1]: a nameless thing does not have a name
example[1]: He lay in a nameless grave.
definition[2]: nameless emotions are very strong and difficult to describe in words
example[2]: He managed to calm her nameless fears.
definition[3]: too terrible to name or describe
